if you don't mind. Right?

929
01:06:15,130 --> 01:06:17,230
OK.

930
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:19,700
Sweetheart,
what has gotten into you?

931
01:06:19,700 --> 01:06:23,340
Nothing. Nothing. Just...

932
01:06:23,340 --> 01:06:23,540
Dad, you can't get married.
It'll totally ruin
completely everything.

933
01:06:27,580 --> 01:06:30,450
Hal. Hal.

934
01:06:30,450 --> 01:06:32,620
Hallie.

935
01:06:32,620 --> 01:06:34,250
Don't look at me.
I don't know a thing.

936
01:06:36,420 --> 01:06:38,990
<i>(music blasts from car stereo)</i>

937
01:06:51,100 --> 01:06:51,740
She thoughtI was going to adopt her?

938
01:06:54,310 --> 01:06:56,210
Hi, doll. - Hi.

939
01:06:58,240 --> 01:06:59,680
Oh. You look stressed, baby.

940
01:07:01,310 --> 01:07:04,550
How about a martini? - How about a double?

941
01:07:08,050 --> 01:07:10,020
Coming right up.

942
01:07:10,020 --> 01:07:10,790
Chessy!

943
01:07:14,090 --> 01:07:18,430
Don't you love it?
It's just what we need,
it's such a big house. Chessy!

944
01:07:19,630 --> 01:07:23,130
You rang? - Two martinis, please.

945
01:07:25,740 --> 01:07:28,170
And make Mr. Parker's
a double.

946
01:07:28,170 --> 01:07:29,640
Chess, please.
I'm getting a migraine.

947
01:07:37,350 --> 01:07:40,450
- I told Hallie.
- You did? And?

948
01:07:40,450 --> 01:07:42,350
She went ballistic.

949
01:07:42,350 --> 01:07:46,060
She started yelling in French.
I didn't even know
she spoke French.

950
01:07:46,060 --> 01:07:48,590
- I don't know what's gotten
into her.
- Oh, Nicky.

951
01:07:48,590 --> 01:07:51,260
This reaction
is totally classic.

952
01:07:51,260 --> 01:07:54,400
It's "Daddy's
Getting Remarried 101."

953
01:07:54,400 --> 01:07:57,270
I'd be worried
if she didn't act this way.

954
01:07:57,270 --> 01:07:59,100
Look.

955
01:07:59,100 --> 01:08:02,510
Why don't I go talk to her?
You know, woman-to-woman.

956
01:08:02,510 --> 01:08:07,240
I think she's a little
sensitive about you right now.

957
01:08:07,250 --> 01:08:12,520
That's why I need to do it.
We've got to
break the ice sometime.

958
01:08:12,520 --> 01:08:17,720
Wear your shirt like this.
I like it when
I can see a little chest hair.

959
01:08:31,640 --> 01:08:34,470
Knock, knock. Can I join you?

960
01:08:34,470 --> 01:08:36,710
Sure.

961
01:08:41,780 --> 01:08:44,510
Guess the news of the
engagement came
as a bit of a shock, huh?

962
01:08:44,520 --> 01:08:46,220
Basically.

963
01:08:46,220 --> 01:08:49,650
You know, I remember
what it was like to be 11.

964
01:08:49,650 --> 01:08:53,290
I had my first beau at 11.
It's a wonderful age.

965
01:08:53,290 --> 01:08:57,230
You're just starting to feel
like a woman and,
believe it or not,

966
01:08:57,230 --> 01:09:00,700
soon you'll understand
what it's like to be in love.

967
01:09:00,700 --> 01:09:02,830
Me? I don't think so.

968
01:09:02,830 --> 01:09:05,540
I don't even have
my 12-year-old molars yet.

969
01:09:05,540 --> 01:09:10,340
Well, take it from someone
who got their molars
very early in life,

970
01:09:10,340 --> 01:09:15,150
being in love is a fantastic
mystery that takes a man
and a woman...

971
01:09:15,150 --> 01:09:19,250
I don't mean to be jerky when
you're trying to be all mushy
and everything,

972
01:09:19,250 --> 01:09:21,320
but I know what mystery
my dad sees in you.

973
01:09:21,320 --> 01:09:23,250
You do?

974
01:09:23,250 --> 01:09:27,290
You're young and beautiful and
sexy and, hey, the guy's
only human.

975
01:09:27,290 --> 01:09:29,690
But if you ask me,

976
01:09:29,690 --> 01:09:31,900
marriage is supposed to
be based on something more
than just sex, right?

977
01:09:31,900 --> 01:09:36,570
Boy, your father
underestimates you.

978
01:09:36,570 --> 01:09:40,570
But you won't.
Will you, Meredith?

979
01:09:40,570 --> 01:09:43,640
Being young and beautiful's
not a crime, you know.

980
01:09:43,640 --> 01:09:47,440
And for your 411,
I adore your father.

981
01:09:47,450 --> 01:09:51,480
He's exactly the kind of man
I always planned on marrying.

982
01:09:51,480 --> 01:09:55,790
This is the real deal, honey.
And nothing you do is going
to come between us.

983
01:09:55,790 --> 01:10:00,660
Hate to break it to you, angel
but you are no longer the only
girl in Nick Parker's life.

984
01:10:00,660 --> 01:10:04,330
- Get over it.
- If this is the real deal,

985
01:10:04,330 --> 01:10:08,930
then my dad's money has
nothing to do with you wanting
to marry him, right?

986
01:10:08,930 --> 01:10:12,740
OK, puss. You listen
and you listen good.

987
01:10:12,740 --> 01:10:16,240
I am marrying your father
in two weeks
whether you like it or not.

988
01:10:16,240 --> 01:10:18,540
So I suggest you do not tangle
with me anymore.

989
01:10:18,540 --> 01:10:19,980
You are in way over your head.
Is that clear?

990
01:10:22,580 --> 01:10:23,980
Crystal.

991
01:10:33,390 --> 01:10:36,490
<i>(Grandfather)</i>Martin!
A refill, please.

992
01:10:41,770 --> 01:10:44,270
- Lovely choice of wine,by the way, Martin.
- Thank you, sir.

993
01:10:44,270 --> 01:10:48,410
- May I have a sip?
- I don't think
you're going to like it.

994
01:10:59,850 --> 01:11:03,890
Well, if you ask me,the bouquet's a little
too robust for a Merlot,

995
01:11:03,890 --> 01:11:07,520
but then again I'm partial to
the softer California grape.

996
01:11:11,400 --> 01:11:13,700
Has she learned about wine
at the summer camp?

997
01:11:13,700 --> 01:11:15,630
She must have.

998
01:11:21,740 --> 01:11:26,310
Darling! Are you all right? - I had one sip too many,
I guess.

999
01:11:26,310 --> 01:11:29,850
You know, Mother,
I feel like I could use
a bit of fresh air.

1000
01:11:29,850 --> 01:11:32,420
Would it be OK if I stepped
outside for a moment?

1001
01:11:32,420 --> 01:11:34,420
Are you OK?
Would you like me
to go with you?

1002
01:11:34,420 --> 01:11:35,990
No, no, no. I'll be fine. Just
got a touch woozy, that's all.

1003
01:11:38,860 --> 01:11:40,290
Woozy, huh?

1004
01:12:04,480 --> 01:12:04,680
I'd like to place a collect call to America,
please.

1005
01:12:07,350 --> 01:12:08,820
<i>(rings)</i>

1006
01:12:11,390 --> 01:12:13,060
- Hello?
- What's up?

1007
01:12:13,060 --> 01:12:16,360
Hal, I'm desperate.
Dad's getting married.

1008
01:12:16,360 --> 01:12:18,360
What do you mean,
getting married?

1009
01:12:18,360 --> 01:12:21,360
I mean black tie, white gown,
the whole enchilada.

1010
01:12:21,370 --> 01:12:23,800
- What?
- <i>The wedding's in two weeks.</i>

1011
01:12:23,800 --> 01:12:27,570
If there's any hope of getting
Mum and Dad back together
we've got to do it fast.

1012
01:12:27,570 --> 01:12:29,640
And I mean really fast.

1013
01:12:29,640 --> 01:12:32,610
OK. So Mom and I are going out
to the theater tonight.

1014
01:12:32,610 --> 01:12:35,380
I'll drop the bomb on her
first thing in the morning.

1015
01:12:35,380 --> 01:12:37,550
<i>OK. Thanks.</i>

1016
01:12:37,550 --> 01:12:37,780
- And, Hallie, hurry!
- OK. I will.

1017
01:12:40,720 --> 01:12:42,020
Oh, excuse me, sir.

1018
01:12:44,460 --> 01:12:47,960
- Uh-oh.
- Uh-oh. Yes.

1019
01:12:47,960 --> 01:12:48,360
Now, what say you and I take
a little stroll in the park,
eh, young lady?

1020
01:12:52,130 --> 01:12:54,900
OK.

1021
01:12:54,900 --> 01:12:56,900
Now...

1022
01:12:56,900 --> 01:12:59,500
Come on,
what's this all about?

1023
01:12:59,500 --> 01:13:01,770
Well, it's a long story.

1024
01:13:01,770 --> 01:13:05,110
Well, it's a very big park
and we've got plenty of time,
you know.

1025
01:13:05,110 --> 01:13:07,510
Well, first of all...

1026
01:13:07,510 --> 01:13:11,880
<i>(Elizabeth) Féminine?
Vraiment... Je ne sais
pas comment expliquer</i>

1027
01:13:11,880 --> 01:13:14,520
<i>mais vous aurez
le dessin demain, en tout cas.</i>

1028
01:13:14,520 --> 01:13:19,690
<i>En satin? Non, non, ce sera
quelque chose plus moderne</i>

1029
01:13:19,690 --> 01:13:24,060
<i>avec de la dentelle, du tulle
blanc très, très jeune,
très léger.</i>

1030
01:13:24,060 --> 01:13:28,000
Just do it, sweet pea.

1031
01:13:28,000 --> 01:13:31,870
<i>Non, c'est trop, non. Oui,
mademoiselle, vous aurez
le dessin demain matin.</i>

1032
01:13:31,870 --> 01:13:36,040
<i>Oui, tout à fait. Ne vous
inquiétez pas. Allez,
au revoir.</i>

1033
01:13:36,040 --> 01:13:39,140
Darling, come in. I just
have to finish this sketch
and fedex it off to Paris.

1034
01:13:39,140 --> 01:13:41,540
Then how about you
and I go out to lunch

1035
01:13:41,550 --> 01:13:45,080
and spend the rest of the day
getting lost in Harrods. Hm?

1036
01:13:45,080 --> 01:13:48,750
I can't, Mum, I'm sorry.
I have to go
out of town today.

1037
01:13:48,750 --> 01:13:51,020
Oh, you have to go
out of town?

1038
01:13:51,020 --> 01:13:54,460
<i>(laughing)</i> And where,
may I ask, are you going?

1039
01:13:54,460 --> 01:13:57,960
Annie. Annie.

1040
01:13:57,960 --> 01:14:01,530
<i>(American accent)</i> That's where
I have to go.
I have to go see Annie.

1041
01:14:01,530 --> 01:14:03,700
I see.
And where might Annie be?

1042
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:07,500
In Napa.
With her father Nick Parker.

1043
01:14:15,180 --> 01:14:18,080
You're not Annie.

1044
01:14:18,080 --> 01:14:21,020
That would be correct.

1045
01:14:21,020 --> 01:14:23,520
You're Hallie?

1046
01:14:23,520 --> 01:14:24,890
I am.

1047
01:14:28,490 --> 01:14:29,460
Annie and I met up at camp and
we decided to switch places.

1048
01:14:34,970 --> 01:14:35,670
I'm sorry, but I'd never seen you, and I dreamt of meeting
you my whole life.

1049
01:14:41,110 --> 01:14:42,210
Annie felt the exact same way about Dad, so we sorta
just switched lives.

1050
01:14:47,240 --> 01:14:49,880
I hope you're not mad, because I love you so much

1051
01:14:49,880 --> 01:14:53,150
and I just hope that one day
you can love me as me,

1052
01:14:53,150 --> 01:14:55,890
and not as Annie.

1053
01:14:55,890 --> 01:14:58,890
Oh, darling.

1054
01:14:58,890 --> 01:15:00,760
I've loved you
your whole life.

1055
01:15:01,560 --> 01:15:04,890
<i>(sobbing)</i>

1056
01:15:07,160 --> 01:15:09,530
I've never been so happy
in my entire life.

1057
01:15:14,040 --> 01:15:16,610
<i>(wails)</i>

1058
01:15:16,610 --> 01:15:17,810
So, I...

1059
01:15:19,780 --> 01:15:24,550
I guess you have
to switch us back now, huh?

1060
01:15:24,550 --> 01:15:25,010
Well, technically, you belong
to your dad and Annie
belongs to me.

1061
01:15:30,550 --> 01:15:31,090
His and hers kids. No offense, Mom, but this arrangement
really sucks.

1062
01:15:35,660 --> 01:15:38,700
I agree. It totally sucks.

1063
01:15:38,700 --> 01:15:44,000
Then I say we fly to Napa,
see Annie and Dad, and work
this whole thing out.

1064
01:15:44,000 --> 01:15:48,070
And I say you're right.
Not to worry, darling.
I'll take care of everything.

1065
01:15:48,070 --> 01:15:50,640
You're not to worry, OK?

1066
01:15:54,880 --> 01:15:57,750
I'm sorry.
I can't handle this.

1067
01:15:57,750 --> 01:16:00,980
I mean, I haven't seen
or heard from Nick Parker
in over 11 years,

1068
01:16:00,990 --> 01:16:04,090
and suddenly I'm flying
halfway across the world to...

1069
01:16:04,090 --> 01:16:06,620
I'm not mature
enough for this.

1070
01:16:06,620 --> 01:16:09,890
If the man didn't make me
so nuts, I'd still be married
to him.

1071
01:16:09,890 --> 01:16:14,200
I mean, we came up with this
arrangement

1072
01:16:14,200 --> 01:16:17,000
so that we'd never
have to see each other again. I mean, look at me, Martin.
Have you ever seen me
like this?

1073
01:16:17,000 --> 01:16:19,200
- Well...
- Don't answer that.

1074
01:16:19,200 --> 01:16:21,940
I mean, what if he doesn't
recognize me?

1075
01:16:21,940 --> 01:16:24,570
No, don't answer that, either.

1076
01:16:24,580 --> 01:16:28,650
So, Hallie said
he was a... a hunk.

1077
01:16:28,650 --> 01:16:31,080
He was rather dishy.

1078
01:16:31,080 --> 01:16:34,350
He had a smile that made me
go weak at the knees,
if you can imagine that.

1079
01:16:34,350 --> 01:16:38,120
- OK. I'm all set, Mom.
- Great. Me too. Almost.

1080
01:16:38,120 --> 01:16:41,190
Mom, your suitcase is,
like, totally empty.

1081
01:16:41,190 --> 01:16:43,860
Oh. Right. Sorry. Um...

1082
01:16:43,860 --> 01:16:45,800
Did you speak to your father,
dear?

1083
01:16:45,800 --> 01:16:48,160
Um... Yeah, yeah.
I just hung up with him,
actually.

1084
01:16:48,170 --> 01:16:51,030
He said he's really anxious
to see you.

1085
01:16:51,040 --> 01:16:54,000
Anxious nervous,
like he's totally,
completely dreading it?

1086
01:16:54,000 --> 01:16:57,140
Or anxious excited,
like he's looking forward
to it?

1087
01:16:57,140 --> 01:17:00,180
- Anxious excited. Definitely.
- Oh.

1088
01:17:00,180 --> 01:17:04,810
He said he'll meet us tomorrow
at noon at the Stafford Hotel
in San Francisco.

1089
01:17:04,820 --> 01:17:07,980
My, my, my. That's incredibly
soon, isn't it?
Well. Um...

1090
01:17:07,990 --> 01:17:10,390
Why don't you run downstairs
and gather up our tickets

1091
01:17:10,390 --> 01:17:12,720
from your grandfather
while I finish up here?

1092
01:17:12,720 --> 01:17:18,030
OK.

1093
01:17:18,030 --> 01:17:22,230
- <i>(whispers)</i> Liar, liar,
pants on fire.
- Sh! Oh, Martin, I have a really
ridiculous, somewhat childish
request to make.

1094
01:17:22,230 --> 01:17:24,800
Martin, you know that you're
more than a butler to me.

1095
01:17:24,800 --> 01:17:27,340
You're more like a lovable
brother who just happens
to wait on us and...

1096
01:17:27,340 --> 01:17:28,770
Anyway, I was wondering if...

1097
01:17:28,770 --> 01:17:30,010
I'd accompany you on the trip?

1098
01:17:30,010 --> 01:17:31,340
Make it a bit easier for you?

1099
01:17:31,340 --> 01:17:34,140
Would you, Martin?
Thank you so much.

1100
01:17:34,140 --> 01:17:37,380
I'd be so grateful. And you
don't even have to come as our
butler, just as a friend.

1101
01:17:37,380 --> 01:17:41,080
Madam, I'd be honored.
And may I say, as a friend,

1102
01:17:41,090 --> 01:17:42,720
if I was seeing my ex,
after 11 years,
and I had your legs...

1103
01:17:45,920 --> 01:17:47,090
I'd wear this little baby.

1104
01:17:49,660 --> 01:17:51,090
You'll kill in it.

1105
01:17:59,070 --> 01:18:01,300
Bye, Daddy, darling. - Bye, darling.

1106
01:18:01,310 --> 01:18:03,740
- Wish me luck.
- Good luck.

1107
01:18:07,440 --> 01:18:09,410
- Bye, Pop.
- Bye, Hal.

1108
01:18:09,410 --> 01:18:11,380
So you're coming to Napa
for Thanksgiving, right?

1109
01:18:11,380 --> 01:18:13,920
I wouldn't miss
it for the world.

1110
01:18:13,920 --> 01:18:15,150
Bye.

1111
01:18:18,090 --> 01:18:20,690
Oh, and say hello
to your father for me.

1112
01:18:20,690 --> 01:18:22,730
I will.

1113
01:18:31,270 --> 01:18:33,470
Airport, please.

1114
01:18:39,410 --> 01:18:41,810
<i>( "In the Mood"
by Joe Garland)</i>

1115
01:18:53,160 --> 01:18:55,390
OK. They'll be here any minute.

1116
01:18:55,390 --> 01:18:58,130
Now, be nice, Daddy.

1117
01:18:58,130 --> 01:19:01,830
He's everything you ever
wanted for your little girl,
plus millions more.

1118
01:19:01,830 --> 01:19:04,230
Then you know I'll be nice.

1119
01:19:04,230 --> 01:19:05,370
Oh, OK. There he is.

1120
01:19:07,910 --> 01:19:09,410
<i>(Sammy barks)</i>

1121
01:19:09,410 --> 01:19:10,070
With the whole motley crew.

1122
01:19:11,840 --> 01:19:14,180
Hi, darling.

1123
01:19:17,250 --> 01:19:18,250
Hallie. Chessy. And Sammy.
What in the world
are you doing here?

1124
01:19:22,850 --> 01:19:24,920
Honey, a dog at the Stafford?

1125
01:19:24,920 --> 01:19:28,120
- Hal begged me to bring him.
- Oh, you're such a softy.

1126
01:19:28,130 --> 01:19:29,830
<i>(Sammy growls)
</i>- Oh!

1127
01:19:29,830 --> 01:19:32,830
Good doggy. So, Meredith,
these the folks?

1128
01:19:32,830 --> 01:19:36,170
Yes. Mom, Dad,
you finally meet.

1129
01:19:36,170 --> 01:19:40,140
This is my fiancé and the love
of my life, Nicholas Parker.

1130
01:19:40,140 --> 01:19:43,370
Hello, Nicholas.
I'm so pleased to meet you.

1131
01:19:43,370 --> 01:19:45,340
- I'm Vicki.
- Hi.

1132
01:19:45,340 --> 01:19:48,380
And this is Nick's adorable
daughter Hallie.

1133
01:19:48,380 --> 01:19:51,380
This entire prenuptial
get-together was her idea,
I'll have you know.

1134
01:19:51,380 --> 01:19:55,390
How are you, young lady?
We've heard nothing but
wonderful things about you.

1135
01:19:55,390 --> 01:19:59,390
Hello, pet.
You may call me Aunt Vicki.

1136
01:20:11,940 --> 01:20:13,940
Other end, madam. - Whoops.

1137
01:20:20,340 --> 01:20:23,580
That was a great flight,wasn't it? I mean,
it was so quick.

1138
01:20:23,580 --> 01:20:26,420
I've never seen you quite
so thirsty before, madam.

1139
01:20:26,420 --> 01:20:30,390
Well, would you believe,
Martin, darling, I've never
tasted vodka before this trip?

1140
01:20:30,390 --> 01:20:32,420
Could have fooled me, ma'am.

1141
01:20:32,420 --> 01:20:35,060
<i>(Elizabeth)</i> Come on.
Let's rock and roll.

1142
01:20:35,060 --> 01:20:38,430
I am in such major
trouble here.

1143
01:20:38,430 --> 01:20:41,460
If the hotel can do it,
I think that room is perfect
for the wedding.

1144
01:20:41,470 --> 01:20:43,530
Not too big, not too cramped.

1145
01:20:43,530 --> 01:20:45,900
And not that I don't like
the idea of having the wedding
at the house,

1146
01:20:45,900 --> 01:20:49,970
it's just that this
could be amazing.

1147
01:20:49,970 --> 01:20:53,010
So I've already checked us in.
Why don't we go upstairs,
