1373
01:34:21,380 --> 01:34:23,090
Hello.

1374
01:34:25,320 --> 01:34:27,260
Hey.

1375
01:34:29,190 --> 01:34:32,290
So...

1376
01:34:33,860 --> 01:34:35,060
Do you have any idea
where they're taking us?

1377
01:34:37,730 --> 01:34:40,200
- Not a clue.
- Right.

1378
01:34:58,250 --> 01:35:00,320
Where are we?

1379
01:35:04,690 --> 01:35:06,360
This is where we're eating?

1380
01:35:06,360 --> 01:35:08,930
No, actually,

1381
01:35:08,930 --> 01:35:13,370
that's where we're eating.

1382
01:35:13,370 --> 01:35:16,140
<i>(Annie)</i> She's ours for
the night.

1383
01:35:16,140 --> 01:35:16,440
<i>(Nick)</i> Wow. So how exactly
are we paying for this?

1384
01:35:21,080 --> 01:35:23,310
Well, we pooled our allowances.

1385
01:35:23,310 --> 01:35:27,950
- Yeah, right, Annie.
- OK. Grandfather chipped
in a bit.

1386
01:35:27,950 --> 01:35:31,290
- Annie.
- OK. He chipped in a lot.

1387
01:35:31,290 --> 01:35:33,320
<i>(Hallie)</i>Come on.
You guys are gonna love it.

1388
01:35:33,320 --> 01:35:35,790
<i>(Nick)</i> Pretty snazzy.

1389
01:35:35,790 --> 01:35:40,730
Elizabeth and Nick,
your dinner awaits you.

1390
01:35:47,400 --> 01:35:49,140
Girls.

1391
01:35:57,080 --> 01:35:59,250
The table's only set for two.

1392
01:35:59,250 --> 01:36:01,920
Oh. That's the other part of
the surprise.
We're not joining you.

1393
01:36:04,790 --> 01:36:06,320
You're not? - No, but I am.

1394
01:36:09,460 --> 01:36:12,430
Good evening. I'm Chessy,
and I'll be your server
this evening.

1395
01:36:12,430 --> 01:36:16,130
- No wisecracks, please.
- And I am Martin,
your sommelier.

1396
01:36:16,130 --> 01:36:20,270
May I offer you both a taste
of the bubbly in the hope that
you'll get a bit schnockered

1397
01:36:20,270 --> 01:36:23,770
and not fire this lovely lady
and myself

1398
01:36:23,770 --> 01:36:27,510
for following
the orders of these
audacious 11-year-olds?

1399
01:36:27,510 --> 01:36:29,950
Annie, mood music, please.

1400
01:36:34,120 --> 01:36:38,190
<i>( "I Love You
for Sentimental Reasons"
by Linda Ronstadt)</i>

1401
01:36:38,190 --> 01:36:41,960
Just relax.
Sail through time.

1402
01:36:41,960 --> 01:36:44,430
<i>(Hallie)</i> Back to yesteryear.

1403
01:36:50,330 --> 01:36:52,170
- You do get all this,don't you?
- Yes, I'm beginning to.

1404
01:36:54,440 --> 01:36:57,370
They're recreating the night we met.
The boat, the music...

1405
01:37:01,080 --> 01:37:03,280
The help.

1406
01:37:03,280 --> 01:37:05,450
It's so sweet.

1407
01:37:05,450 --> 01:37:05,810
Martin,
I think I'll take that drink.

1408
01:37:08,320 --> 01:37:10,050
Thank you, Martin.

1409
01:37:12,090 --> 01:37:13,390
Oh. Yeah.

1410
01:37:15,460 --> 01:37:19,230
To tell you the truth,I haven't been on a boat
since the <i>QE2.</i>

1411
01:37:23,400 --> 01:37:25,830
Neither have I.

1412
01:37:25,840 --> 01:37:26,940
Well, then, here's to, uh...

1413
01:37:29,340 --> 01:37:32,170
Our daughters.

1414
01:37:32,180 --> 01:37:34,210
Our daughters.

1415
01:37:40,850 --> 01:37:42,620
Now I know how a goldfish feels.

1416
01:37:42,620 --> 01:37:45,620
<i>(groans)</i>

1417
01:37:45,620 --> 01:37:48,290
You know, sometime
if we're ever really alone,

1418
01:37:48,290 --> 01:37:49,360
maybe we could talk about
what happened between us.

1419
01:37:54,100 --> 01:37:56,400
It all feels a bit hazy to me now.

1420
01:37:56,400 --> 01:37:59,630
It ended so fast.

1421
01:37:59,640 --> 01:38:02,200
It started so fast.

1422
01:38:02,210 --> 01:38:05,340
Well, that part
I remember perfectly.

1423
01:38:09,280 --> 01:38:11,410
Looks like things are
heating up
quite nicely.

1424
01:38:11,410 --> 01:38:13,920
I'd say it's safe to serve
the vichyssoise.

1425
01:38:13,920 --> 01:38:15,320
You ladle, I'll serve.

1426
01:38:16,590 --> 01:38:19,420
I'm sorry.

1427
01:38:26,100 --> 01:38:28,530
Yes, I'll ladle.

1428
01:38:28,530 --> 01:38:29,630
Right. And then I'll...

1429
01:38:32,140 --> 01:38:34,240
Serve?- Right.

1430
01:38:35,370 --> 01:38:38,540
Right.

1431
01:38:38,540 --> 01:38:43,650
<i>(Elizabeth)</i> So... you've done
fantastically well.

1432
01:38:43,650 --> 01:38:48,220
Your dream of owning your own
vineyard, it actually
came true.

1433
01:38:48,220 --> 01:38:52,090
What about you? You were
always drawing on napkins
and corners of newspapers.

1434
01:38:52,090 --> 01:38:54,420
Now you're
this major designer.

1435
01:38:54,420 --> 01:38:57,230
Yeah. It's great.

1436
01:38:57,230 --> 01:38:59,960
We both actually got
where we wanted to go.

1437
01:38:59,960 --> 01:39:02,330
Yeah. We did.

1438
01:39:02,330 --> 01:39:04,370
Anyway, what are we going
to do about the girls?

1439
01:39:08,400 --> 01:39:11,340
Well, now that they've met,
we can't very well
keep them apart.

1440
01:39:11,340 --> 01:39:14,710
Well, I could keep them
for half the year, and then
you could keep them for...

1441
01:39:14,710 --> 01:39:18,110
Guys, they can't go to
two different schools
every year. That's nuts.

1442
01:39:18,110 --> 01:39:19,650
I agree.

1443
01:39:19,650 --> 01:39:21,580
Well, I could keep them both
for a whole year, and you...

1444
01:39:21,580 --> 01:39:24,590
- Liz, that's why we came
up with...
- Mm-mm. Mm-hm.

1445
01:39:24,590 --> 01:39:26,390
<i>(clears throat)</i>

1446
01:39:26,390 --> 01:39:30,730
Oh. Sorry. Ignore me.
Enjoy your soup.

1447
01:39:30,730 --> 01:39:34,030
That's why we came up with
the solution that we have.

1448
01:39:34,030 --> 01:39:35,160
Really? I thought it was
because we decided never to
see each other again.

1449
01:39:39,300 --> 01:39:41,700
Not "we," Liz.

1450
01:39:41,700 --> 01:39:45,610
Well, you know, that part's
become a bit hazy to me too
over the years.

1451
01:39:45,610 --> 01:39:47,240
You don't remember the day
you packed?

1452
01:39:47,240 --> 01:39:50,280
No, that day
I remember perfectly.

1453
01:39:50,280 --> 01:39:53,980
Did I hurt you when I threw
that, um...
What was it? A...

1454
01:39:53,980 --> 01:39:56,350
It was a hairdryer.

1455
01:39:56,350 --> 01:39:58,150
Oh. Right.

1456
01:39:58,150 --> 01:39:58,420
Sorry.

1457
01:40:00,160 --> 01:40:03,190
You know, I may never
be alone with you again.

1458
01:40:07,630 --> 01:40:12,700
So, about that day that you
packed... Why'd you do it?

1459
01:40:12,700 --> 01:40:13,470
Oh, Nick. We were so young
and we both had tempers.

1460
01:40:18,270 --> 01:40:21,210
We said stupid things and so I packed.

1461
01:40:21,210 --> 01:40:21,440
Got on my very first
747 and...

1462
01:40:24,280 --> 01:40:25,750
You didn't come after me.

1463
01:40:29,050 --> 01:40:31,150
I didn't know that
you wanted me to.

1464
01:40:31,150 --> 01:40:33,760
Well, it really doesn't matter
anymore.

1465
01:40:36,790 --> 01:40:38,160
So let's just put a good face
on for the girls and get this
show on the road, huh?

1466
01:40:43,170 --> 01:40:47,570
Yeah. Sure. Let's get this show
on the road.

1467
01:40:55,280 --> 01:40:57,250
Your passport, Ms. James.Have a safe trip home.

1468
01:40:57,250 --> 01:40:59,350
Thank you.

1469
01:40:59,350 --> 01:41:00,580
All set, then?
Where's Annie?

1470
01:41:00,580 --> 01:41:03,180
I just rang up.
She's on her way down.

1471
01:41:03,190 --> 01:41:04,720
Right.

1472
01:41:04,720 --> 01:41:07,420
So I'll send Hallie
back to you over Christmas.

1473
01:41:09,560 --> 01:41:12,330
And Annie'll spend Easter
with you.

1474
01:41:12,330 --> 01:41:13,630
<i>(elevator bell)</i>

1475
01:41:15,700 --> 01:41:18,400
Annie, what are you doing in
those clothes? We've got
a plane to catch.

1476
01:41:20,700 --> 01:41:23,340
Here's the deal, Mom.

1477
01:41:23,340 --> 01:41:26,440
We thought it over,
and we decided we're being
totally gypped.

1478
01:41:26,440 --> 01:41:30,380
Dad promised we'd go on our
camping trip, and we wanna go.
Together.

1479
01:41:30,380 --> 01:41:32,210
What camping trip?

1480
01:41:32,210 --> 01:41:34,520
The one we go on
every summer
before school starts.

1481
01:41:34,520 --> 01:41:37,190
Annie, this is ridiculous.
Go upstairs and
put your clothes on.

1482
01:41:37,190 --> 01:41:40,490
- Are you sure I'm Annie?
- Well, of course I'm sure.

1483
01:41:40,490 --> 01:41:43,460
But it's kind of hard
to be 100 percent positive,
isn't it?

1484
01:41:43,460 --> 01:41:48,130
Girls, this is totally
unfunny. You're gonna make
your mother miss her airplane.

1485
01:41:48,130 --> 01:41:49,730
- Annie.
- <i>(both)</i> Yes?

1486
01:41:57,540 --> 01:42:00,210
This one's Hallie. I'm positive.

1487
01:42:00,210 --> 01:42:02,180
You know,
I hope you're right, Dad,

1488
01:42:02,180 --> 01:42:02,340
because you wouldn't wanna
send the wrong kid all the way
back to England.

1489
01:42:06,450 --> 01:42:08,250
Would you?

1490
01:42:14,760 --> 01:42:18,530
Here's our proposition.

1491
01:42:18,530 --> 01:42:20,800
We go back to Dad's house,
pack our stuff,

1492
01:42:20,800 --> 01:42:24,370
and the four of us
leave on the camping trip.

1493
01:42:24,370 --> 01:42:26,640
- The four of us?
- And when you bring us back,

1494
01:42:26,640 --> 01:42:28,700
we'll tell you who's Annie
and who's Hallie.

1495
01:42:28,700 --> 01:42:32,270
Or you do as we say,
and I take one of you back
with me to London,

1496
01:42:32,270 --> 01:42:34,780
whether you like it or not.

1497
01:42:41,180 --> 01:42:44,250
And what am I supposed to do for three days?
Sit home and knit?

1498
01:42:44,250 --> 01:42:47,160
Honey, we have kind
of a sticky situation.

1499
01:42:47,160 --> 01:42:49,190
Sticky situation? What do you
mean, sticky situation?
What exactly...?

1500
01:42:51,930 --> 01:42:53,700
Excuse me. What is she doing here?

1501
01:42:56,430 --> 01:43:00,870
You see, that's part
of the deal. The four of us,
we go together.

1502
01:43:00,870 --> 01:43:02,700
What are you,
suddenly the Brady Bunch?
This is ridic...

1503
01:43:02,710 --> 01:43:05,340
Hello. Everything all right?

1504
01:43:05,340 --> 01:43:07,580
Well, no, actually, it isn't.

1505
01:43:07,580 --> 01:43:10,910
I didn't realize that
you were going
on this little outing,

1506
01:43:10,910 --> 01:43:13,620
and to tell you the truth
I'm not so sure that I'm OK
with it.

1507
01:43:13,620 --> 01:43:15,750
I agree.

1508
01:43:15,750 --> 01:43:18,890
I think the ex-wife
in the next sleeping bag
is a little weird.

1509
01:43:18,890 --> 01:43:21,960
- Thank you.
- I absolutely insist
that you come with us.

1510
01:43:21,960 --> 01:43:24,530
- Really.
- Liz...

1511
01:43:24,530 --> 01:43:28,460
No, honestly, Nick, I've
messed up your entire weekend.
It's the least I can do.

1512
01:43:28,460 --> 01:43:30,500
Really. Please.

1513
01:43:42,410 --> 01:43:45,950
- Dad, what's Meredith doing here?
- Your mother invited her.

1514
01:43:45,950 --> 01:43:47,250
What?

1515
01:43:47,250 --> 01:43:47,620
Be nice.

1516
01:44:01,600 --> 01:44:05,230
OK. All set? Have fun, everyone.

1517
01:44:05,230 --> 01:44:08,270
- What?
- Liz, what are you doing?

1518
01:44:08,270 --> 01:44:11,910
Well, I really think that you
and Meredith need some time
alone before the big day.

1519
01:44:11,910 --> 01:44:14,640
Mom, come on.
That's not the plan.

1520
01:44:14,640 --> 01:44:17,350
Oh, honestly, you'll have much
more fun without me.

1521
01:44:17,350 --> 01:44:19,750
Wait, wait. If you're
not going, I certainly don't
have to go.

1522
01:44:19,750 --> 01:44:22,350
I mean, trust me,
I'm not a big nature girl.

1523
01:44:22,350 --> 01:44:24,820
But this is your chance
to really get
to know the girls.

1524
01:44:24,820 --> 01:44:29,260
I mean, after all, starting
next week they're...
they're half yours.

1525
01:44:34,600 --> 01:44:37,330
Have fun, all of you.

1526
01:44:41,540 --> 01:44:43,910
Bye-bye.

1527
01:44:43,910 --> 01:44:44,370
Oh, I would pay big money
to see that woman
climb a mountain.

1528
01:44:47,510 --> 01:44:49,540
- <i>(Nick)</i> Don't hurry, honey.
- <i>(Annie)</i>OK.

1529
01:44:56,390 --> 01:44:58,020
Whoa!

1530
01:44:58,020 --> 01:44:59,890
Come on, you guys.

1531
01:44:59,890 --> 01:45:01,920
Whoa. Whoa.

1532
01:45:16,510 --> 01:45:18,770
I'm gonna kill my trainer.

1533
01:45:18,770 --> 01:45:21,940
He says
I'm in such great shape.

1534
01:45:21,940 --> 01:45:25,480
I can't believe people
actually do this for fun.

1535
01:45:25,480 --> 01:45:27,750
Hold on. We're stopping.

1536
01:45:27,750 --> 01:45:33,350
Again? Dad, at this rate
it'll take us three days
just to get to the lake.

1537
01:45:33,360 --> 01:45:35,820
<i>(Nick)</i> Meredith isn't used
to the altitude. Just chill.

1538
01:45:35,830 --> 01:45:37,460
OK?

1539
01:45:37,460 --> 01:45:37,690
<i>(Meredith groans)</i>

1540
01:45:39,500 --> 01:45:41,960
Oh, I'm in serious pain.

1541
01:45:45,370 --> 01:45:47,400
Somebody hand me my Evian.

1542
01:45:47,400 --> 01:45:49,400
I can't move.

1543
01:45:49,410 --> 01:45:51,510
Sure.

1544
01:45:56,610 --> 01:45:58,550
<i>(whispers)</i> Brilliant.

1545
01:46:03,020 --> 01:46:05,420
Here you go, Mer.

1546
01:46:12,960 --> 01:46:15,500
Honey, you OK?

1547
01:46:15,500 --> 01:46:19,470
- What happened?
- This little guy was
on her Evian bottle.

1548
01:46:19,470 --> 01:46:22,370
Oh. He won't hurt you, Mer.

1549
01:46:22,370 --> 01:46:24,140
Oh, right, right, right.
I... I know.

1550
01:46:24,140 --> 01:46:25,670
You...

1551
01:46:25,670 --> 01:46:27,880
go ahead.

1552
01:46:27,880 --> 01:46:30,750
I'll be fine.

1553
01:46:30,750 --> 01:46:34,850
Get that thing away from me.
I hate things that crawl. Ugh.

1554
01:46:34,850 --> 01:46:37,120
How can you touch that?
Just... put it down.

1555
01:46:37,120 --> 01:46:38,650
OK, OK, I'll put it down.

1556
01:46:39,690 --> 01:46:43,160
- <i>(Nick)</i> Girls...
- What?

1557
01:46:44,660 --> 01:46:46,830
- What?
- I'm going to take the lead.

1558
01:46:46,830 --> 01:46:49,860
The two of you help Meredith.
All right?

1559
01:46:49,870 --> 01:46:50,730
Sure you'll help me.
Right over a cliff,
you'll help me.

1560
01:46:55,540 --> 01:46:57,670
Not a bad idea. - Yeah. See any cliffs?

1561
01:46:57,670 --> 01:47:00,810
Oh, my backpack.

1562
01:47:00,810 --> 01:47:03,010
Need a hand, Mer?

1563
01:47:03,010 --> 01:47:04,010
Not from you, thank you.

1564
01:47:06,750 --> 01:47:09,950
Don't think I can't see right
past those angelic faces.

1565
01:47:09,950 --> 01:47:13,720
One more trick from you two
and I promise I will make
your lives miserable

1566
01:47:13,720 --> 01:47:16,460
from the day I say, "I do."

1567
01:47:16,460 --> 01:47:16,990
Got it?

1568
01:47:18,430 --> 01:47:19,860
Got it, Cruella.

1569
01:47:21,630 --> 01:47:23,930
What did you call me?

1570
01:47:27,070 --> 01:47:30,140
<i>(Hallie)</i>Nothing, nothing.
Not a thing, Cruella.

1571
01:47:30,140 --> 01:47:32,670
Oh, by the way, Mer,

1572
01:47:32,680 --> 01:47:35,080
I think there's something
on your head.

1573
01:47:50,230 --> 01:47:51,930
Are you all right?

1574
01:47:52,590 --> 01:47:56,100
What... happened?

1575
01:47:58,500 --> 01:48:00,470
Ask them.

1576
01:48:02,670 --> 01:48:03,570
<i>(coughs)</i>

1577
01:48:05,640 --> 01:48:08,710
What did we do, Dad?We were right behind you.

1578
01:48:12,080 --> 01:48:13,980
This is really good. - Yeah, I know.

1579
01:48:17,050 --> 01:48:20,860
Here we go, girls.
This'll hold us for a while.

1580
01:48:24,930 --> 01:48:27,160
Sure you don't want
some trout, Mom?

1581
01:48:27,160 --> 01:48:30,530
Is that OK, by the way,
if we start calling you Mom?

1582
01:48:30,530 --> 01:48:33,070
I think your mother would
prefer if you called me
Meredith.

1583
01:48:33,070 --> 01:48:34,570
And no, thank you,
I do not eat trout,
for the thousandth time.

1584
01:48:39,540 --> 01:48:42,140
I will wait until breakfast. What are we having?

1585
01:48:42,140 --> 01:48:44,710
- <i>(all)</i> Trout.
- Oh.

1586
01:48:44,710 --> 01:48:46,150
Come on, it's part
of the experience.

1587
01:48:46,150 --> 01:48:48,520
Mm, and what's the other part?

1588
01:48:48,520 --> 01:48:52,250
Being eaten to death by
mosquitoes? God, you'd think
they actually like this stuff.

1589
01:48:52,250 --> 01:48:54,760
Well, what's that
you're using?
Here, let me see that.

1590
01:48:56,660 --> 01:49:00,130
You're gonna attract every mosquito in the state
with this stuff.

1591
01:49:02,160 --> 01:49:04,270
It's sugar and water.

1592
01:49:04,270 --> 01:49:08,000
Where'd you get it?

1593
01:49:08,000 --> 01:49:13,710
That's it. I am taking
one large sleeping pill
and going to bed.

1594
01:49:19,950 --> 01:49:22,320
Meredith?

1595
01:49:22,320 --> 01:49:24,220
What are you doing?

1596
01:49:24,220 --> 01:49:28,790
I don't want
the mountain lions to...

1597
01:49:28,790 --> 01:49:29,090
There are no mountain lions
up here, are there?

1598
01:49:31,590 --> 01:49:33,060
No.

1599
01:49:50,710 --> 01:49:52,750
Good night.

1600
01:49:57,090 --> 01:50:00,790
Girls, I'm telling you,
lay off.

1601
01:50:00,790 --> 01:50:04,660
This isn't her thing, OK?
I'm not marrying her because
she's Annie Oakley.

1602
01:50:04,660 --> 01:50:08,060
- Who's Annie Oakley?
- Just cool it.

1603
01:50:25,880 --> 01:50:28,050
Come on, come on. - <i>(Annie)</i> OK.

1604
01:50:28,050 --> 01:50:30,380
